results.name: a(n) = 1 if 10^(2^n)+1 is prime, otherwise smallest prime factor of 10^(2^n)+1.
comment: 10^(2^14)+1 is composite, but no prime factors are known. The smallest known prime factors of 10^(2^15)+1 to 10^(2^18)+1 are 65537, 8257537, 175636481, 639631361. [_Jeppe Stig Nielsen_, Nov 04 2010]
Above values for a(15)-a(18) are confirmed. a(19) = 70254593, a(20) = 167772161. - _Chai Wah Wu_, Oct 16 2019
link: Wilfrid Keller, Prime factors of generalized Fermat numbers Fm(10) and complete factoring status
